cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper is about natural language processing and specifically focuses on natural language inference using deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a special LSTM architecture for NLI, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses neural attention models, which could also make it relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of LSTMs also suggests that it could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses the Stanford Natural Language Inference (SNLI) corpus, which could make it relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as well, since NLI is often used in image captioning tasks.
